          <p><em>From <a href="https://code.google.com/u/105092052613467789971/">pjalaran...@gmail.com</a> on August 10, 2012 02:26:53</em></p>

<p>I have already implement rotation successfully. What I did was implement a rotation to MapViewCanvas in FrameBuffer.java<br>
It rotates according to screen center. I am now working in a way to do the correct rotation according to user heading. I hope I can end this next week because it is a feature I need for a project I have to deliver in september.</p>

<p>If some one was information about user heading using north grid please give some feedback.</p>

<p>Here goes the method <br>
public void canvasRotation(float heading, int screenCenterX,int screenCenterY) {<br><br>
     mapViewCanvas.rotate(heading, screenCenterX, screenCenterY);<br><br>
    } </p>

<p>I still have some problems:</p>

<ul>
<li>tiles anti-aliasing (rotation gives an odd look to the tiles) </li>
<li>rotation animation</li>
<li>correct user heading according to map coordinates.</li>
</ul>
      </div>
