  </div>
</div>


  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p>I agree that it appears to be number 1 feature that people want from the map client.</p>

<p>We intend to revisit this feature after the official release of 0.5 version.<br>
But it depends on the work to be done with the <code>LabelLayer</code> in order to proper rotate only some map elements below  and not the horizontal labels or the symbols above.</p>

<p>Currently I use a custom map rotation from old days based on Google sample,<br>
by hosting the map view in another view of which the canvas is rotated.<br>
I describe this solution in a discussion at mailing list:<br>
<a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!msg/mapsforge-dev/hUgOBa4Pmj8/I2uH6NYs3uQJ">https://groups.google.com/forum/#!msg/mapsforge-dev/hUgOBa4Pmj8/I2uH6NYs3uQJ</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>

