    <strong>
      <a href="/ludwigb" class="author">ludwigb</a>
    </strong>

    commented

    <a href="#issuecomment-93760715" class="timestamp">
      <time datetime="2015-04-16T15:16:33Z" is="relative-time">Apr 16, 2015</time>
    </a>
  </div>
</div>


  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body email-format js-comment-body">
          <div class="email-fragment">I kind of got stuck on this, feel free to try it out.

The problem is that the various scaling and rotation events screw up the
label positioning (e.g. try rotating the map in the Samples app and you
will see that the points do not cleanly revolve around the center).

I think also an interface is needed to retrieve label data directly from
the map file (rather than go through this strange caching via the tile
rendering). But while this is not so difficult for some map zoom levels, I
do not understand the format well enough to do this for some of the
intermediate zoom levels where data from different tiles has to be
combined.

Ludwig</div>
